│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue: The problem is in the `processSwitch` function in correlated-value-propagation. When removing a switch case that is a self-loop (case destination equals the switch block),        │
│ calling `removePredecessor` on the block itself causes issues. Specifically, when `Succ == BB` (self-loop), `Succ->removePredecessor(BB)` tries to remove `BB` as a predecessor of itself. While this might    │
│ seem harmless, it can trigger PHI node simplification in other blocks (like `loop` in this example) because removing a self-loop edge might make certain CFG edges unreachable, leading to further             │
│ simplifications that crash.                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The transformation incorrectly determines that the switch's default destination is unreachable and replaces it with an unreachable block. This changes well-defined behavior (going  │
│ to `exit` when `%phi = -1`) to undefined behavior. The root cause is that after removing the self-loop case (case 0), the analysis incorrectly computes that the remaining cases (1 and 2) cover all possible  │
│ values of `%phi`, which they don't (`%phi` is only -1 or 0, not 1 or 2).                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis: There are actually two related issues:                                                                                                                                                 │
│    a) The self-loop removal triggers unexpected PHI simplification in other blocks.                                                                                                                            │
│    b) The logic for determining if the default is unreachable is flawed: it only compares the size of the value range with the number of reachable cases, not whether the cases actually cover the range.      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│    However, the immediate crash is caused by (a). When `removePredecessor` is called with `Succ == BB`, it can have side effects on other blocks due to PHI simplification. In this case, the PHI in `loop`    │
│ gets simplified to constant `-1`, and when its uses are replaced, something goes wrong (possibly because the switch is being modified concurrently).                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The fix is to skip the `removePredecessor` call when removing a self-loop case, since a block cannot be its own predecessor in a meaningful way for PHI updates. A self-loop edge   │
│ doesn't contribute to PHI nodes in the block itself (a PHI in a block can't reference the same block as an incoming edge). So we can safely skip this call.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│    Edit `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/CorrelatedValuePropagation.cpp` line 384:                                                                                                                                  │
│    ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│    if (Succ != BB)                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│      Succ->removePredecessor(BB);                                                                                                                                                                              │
│    ```                                                                                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│    This prevents the problematic `removePredecessor` call when removing a self-loop case.                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 5. Conclusion: Adding a check to avoid calling `removePredecessor` for self-loop cases fixes the crash. The self-loop edge removal doesn't require PHI updates because a block can't have PHI entries from     │
│ itself. This is a safe fix that prevents the cascade of transformations that leads to the crash.                                                                                                               │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                                                                │
